body:
Running a biz with your partner is tough—and can be seen as a liability. After all, soured relationships have destroyed many a startup. 💔

@jaimeschmidt and I were even advised to not reveal that we were married while growing ours.

But for us, it was an advantage. Five tips. 👇

@ulhas_sm Unsolicited tips
1. Give signing bonuses that accrue fully prorated at 6 months post joining 
2. Roll out multiple offers for the same position. If 1 or 2 drop out you're safe. If 2/3 people join - anyway as a startup your needs would keep increasing. Fire a few later if needed.
